The paper discusses the explicability of a classification system built from neural networks, which is a topic that falls under the sub-categories of machine learning (cs.LG), computer vision (cs.CV), artificial intelligence (cs.AI), neural and evolutionary computing (cs.NE), and systems and control (cs.SY). The use of convolutional neural networks also suggests a focus on computer vision, which further supports the likelihood of cs.CV being the most relevant sub-category.
